      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean \"overwhelmingly agree\" seems a bit strong, doesn't it? weren't there significant debates among scholars about whether the legislative wins actually fixed the systemic stuff, or if it just moved the goalposts? seems like there's a lot of disagreement on whether the movement actually \"succeeded\" in a meaningful way for most people.",
